In the limit , the s-brane wave functions may
be understood in terms of a flux matching procedure.
A similar procedure was used to study scattering of scalar
fields by a D3 brane in . 
In this limit the Klein-Gordon equation  describes brane creation
 in the far past and brane decay in the far future, separated
by a long region near  where the interaction is negligible.
Approximate solutions to  may be found by matching
wave functions of brane creation with wave functions of brane decay
across the region .
In particular,  and 
