Thermal correlators  

We will now demonstrate that the correlators of the 
vacuum are asymptotically thermal in the far future. The theory is
free, so it suffices to consider the two point function .
For brane creation, we have  u_-^in  = a ( u_-^out  -
e^-2+i  u_-^out  ^* ) 

so the  Green function is 
G_-^in (x,y) =& d^d-1  u^in (x) u^in  ^*(y) =&
