Eliminating the Hagedorn divergence 
 It is interesting to note that at , the problem of
Hagedorn type divergences in open string pair production disappear,
simply because there is no
brane present at real  and therefore no open string pair
production.  This can also be seen from looking at the closed string
channel of the annulus.
The breakdown  of  string
perturbation theory at  can be seen 
from looking at the annulus diagram Z(T)=-B_2/T  dq e^q(L_0+L_0)   B_2/T 
.  When , a   acquires a component with a zero
eigenvalue of . This leads to the divergence in
 which signals the breakdown of perturbation theory.

However for the special value , this
divergence is absent. In that case  and 
vanish, so there are no massless modes in the closed string
channel of .

